crt: add missing __MINGW_IMP_SYMBOL for _strtof_l and _wcstof_l

These functions are static emulations present in every libmsvcr*.a,
but the headers declare them dllimport (_CRTIMP), so callers reference
__imp__strtof_l and __imp__wcstof_l, which nothing defines, and the
link fails. Define fake import pointers alongside the definitions, as
already done for other statically-emulated functions such as
__acrt_iob_func and _initialize_onexit_table.

The _strtof_l half was merged upstream after v14.0.0 as 373c7dd0
("crt: Add missing __MINGW_IMP_SYMBOL for _strtof_l()"). The
_wcstof_l half is the same fix for the wide variant, which remains
broken upstream.

--- a/mingw-w64-crt/stdio/_strtof_l.c
+++ b/mingw-w64-crt/stdio/_strtof_l.c
@@ -26,3 +26,5 @@
   }
   return ret;
 }
+
+float (*__MINGW_IMP_SYMBOL(_strtof_l))(const char *, char **, _locale_t) = _strtof_l;
--- a/mingw-w64-crt/stdio/_wcstof_l.c
+++ b/mingw-w64-crt/stdio/_wcstof_l.c
@@ -26,3 +26,5 @@
   }
   return ret;
 }
+
+float (*__MINGW_IMP_SYMBOL(_wcstof_l))(const wchar_t *, wchar_t **, _locale_t) = _wcstof_l;
